{"disposition":"accepted","experiment_id":"WM-001","findings":[{"id":"F001","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.17 independent rehearsal verifier read matrix_contract_sha256 from the performance-free formal-binding v10 development projection, where the schema deliberately forbids that member, and therefore rejected a valid launcher-accepted result."},{"id":"F002","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.17 unit and subprocess fixtures invented the forbidden development-projection member, so producer and consumer fixtures agreed with each other while diverging from the exact production binding schema."},{"id":"F003","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The v1.18 independent verifier obtains the matrix identity from verify_protocol only after the raw-byte protocol seal and fixed matrix invariant pass, while verify_binding continues to authenticate the binding's exact protocol digest and formal-binding v10 shape."},{"id":"F004","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"The decisive v1.18 integration fixture has the exact 26-field no-additional-property development projection, proves launcher-stored stdout is byte-identical to the supplied child output, and requires those stored bytes to pass the separate independent verifier."},{"id":"F005","resolution":"resolved","severity":"major","summary":"A negative regression rewrites the nested fresh-runtime matrix identity and its dependent hashes yet the independent verifier still rejects it, closing the acceptance-only gap."},{"id":"F006","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The protocol directly supersedes the exact sealed v1.17 digest, fresh v1.18 master seeds reproduce from the declared SHA-256 derivation, and central verifier and independent auditor retain identical prior master tuples through v1.17 with 170 prior masters and 23,120 prior streams."},{"id":"F007","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"All 17 scientific protocol blocks and the four scientific kernel files remain byte-identical to the sealed v1.4 system; formal-binding v10, raw-result v9, protocol v9, preformal v2, and formal-launch v3 representation identities remain unchanged."},{"id":"F008","resolution":"resolved","severity":"minor","summary":"Repository status documentation now identifies v1.18 as the active prospective successor and the operator runbook preserves the one-shot rehearsal, recovery, formal-path absence, and post-rehearsal launch ordering."},{"id":"F009","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"Fresh separate QA and runtime environments contain the same reviewed Prospect distribution, and the regenerated runtime lock verifies the installed runtime closure; QA-only tools remain outside the producer closure by design."},{"id":"F010","resolution":"informational","severity":"note","summary":"The declared trust model remains cooperative single-principal custody without hostile-writer resistance or external attestation; v1.18 does not overstate that boundary."}],"implementation_files":[{"bytes":1685,"path":"Makefile","sha256":"18a0068d858da32934717fac69bc3c43c4c27d429e063586e46781a56d6ab12f"},{"bytes":148,"path":"bench/__init__.py","sha256":"6c7b9de75c247ced5f62064f9786cf6e2f14d958bd1be6eb65c6ed69680b6942"},{"bytes":561,"path":"bench/epistemic/__init__.py","sha256":"bb77dc8aba3b32b6bc2df16a5abd9fc24b0ece2a389e814c3337a0f637a5467e"},{"bytes":44718,"path":"bench/epistemic/lifecycle.py","sha256":"3d30d947ca830a0c307f2e7f40d31bc4bef51d497f2e96d68f000fa864e3ed25"},{"bytes":30661,"path":"bench/epistemic/maturity.py","sha256":"2a81abe60f12285f66f2bcd351589de28851412f1d9df7f2003843a845a2510e"},{"bytes":13611,"path":"bench/epistemic/problem.py","sha256":"c66ae13d3e833ffd1be1562a89e0e9035d6197b95723179b930c1ca2a1059c66"},{"bytes":1097,"path":"bench/epistemic/run_maturity.py","sha256":"86ae2c3175262f559a274827c96c30212fbdb9250e3a4614f92c861b7498feb7"},{"bytes":20656,"path":"bench/epistemic